* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The energy required to compress three carbon-carbon single bonds and stretch three carbon-carbon double bonds to the benzene bond length of 1.397 Å is calculated using the harmonic oscillator potential energy formula \( E = \frac{1}{2} k (\Delta x)^2 \), where \( k \) is the force constant and \( \Delta x \) is the change in bond length.

For the single bonds (typical length 1.53 Å, force constant 500 N/m):
- Change in length: \( |1.397 - 1.53| = 0.133 \, \text{Å} = 1.33 \times 10^{-11} \, \text{m} \)
- Energy per bond: \( E_{\text{single}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 500 \times (1.33 \times 10^{-11})^2 = 4.422 \times 10^{-20} \, \text{J} \)
- Energy for three bonds: \( 3 \times 4.422 \times 10^{-20} = 1.3266 \times 10^{-19} \, \text{J} \)

For the double bonds (typical length 1.335 Å, force constant 950 N/m):
- Change in length: \( |1.397 - 1.335| = 0.062 \, \text{Å} = 6.2 \times 10^{-12} \, \text{m} \)
- Energy per bond: \( E_{\text{double}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 950 \times (6.2 \times 10^{-12})^2 = 1.8259 \times 10^{-20} \, \text{J} \)
- Energy for three bonds: \( 3 \times 1.8259 \times 10^{-20} = 5.4777 \times 10^{-20} \, \text{J} \)

Total energy per molecule: \( 1.3266 \times 10^{-19} + 5.4777 \times 10^{-20} = 1.8744 \times 10^{-19} \, \text{J} \)

Convert to energy per mole:
- Avogadro's number: \( 6.022 \times 10^{23} \, \text{mol}^{-1} \)
- Energy in J/mol: \( 1.8744 \times 10^{-19} \times 6.022 \times 10^{23} = 112,879 \, \text{J/mol} \)

