\[
P\left(\left| \frac{Y}{n} - 0.25 \right| \geq 0.05\right) \leq \frac{\sigma^2}{\epsilon^2} = \frac{0.000375}{(0.05)^2} = \frac{0.000375}{0.0025} = 0.15
\]

Thus,

\[
P\left(\left| \frac{Y}{n} - 0.25 \right| < 0.05\right) \geq 1 - 0.15 = 0.85
\]

The value 0.85 is the lower bound, rounded to two significant figures.

