Solution: The sample mean \(\bar{X}\) of a random sample of size 12 from the uniform distribution on \((0,1)\) has a mean \(\mu = 0.5\) and variance \(\sigma^2 / n = (1/12) / 12 = 1/144\), so the standard deviation is \(\sigma_{\bar{X}} = 1/12\).

