- The interval \([0, L/3]\) has length \(L/3\).
- The interval \([2L/3, L]\) has length \(L/3\).

The total length where the condition holds is \(L/3 + L/3 = 2L/3\). The probability is \((2L/3) / L = 2/3\).

Evaluating \(2/3\) to a decimal and rounding to three significant figures gives \(0.667\).

